{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T07:22:19.750Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Normalization (LayerNorm)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a normalization technique that normalizes activations "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "across the feature dimension within a single sample"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", rather than across the batch. Unlike Batch Norm, it computes mean and variance using all features in a layer for each individual data point, making it "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "independent of batch size"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and ideal for sequence models like Transformers and RNNs.)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Layer Norm — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Layer Norm Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm normalizes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "horizontally"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across features for each sample independently:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Take activations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from a layer for a single sample"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Calculate mean and variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " across all features in that layer (for that sample)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalize"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": subtract mean, divide by standard deviation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scale and shift"}, {"type": "text", "text": " using learnable parameters γ and β"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Difference: Layer Norm vs. Batch Norm"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalization axis"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vertical"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": across batch dimension"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Horizontal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": across feature dimension"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Statistics computed over"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All samples in batch (per feature)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All features in one sample)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size dependency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Yes (needs batch > 1)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ No (works with batch=1)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "CNNs, MLPs (fixed-size images)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers, RNNs, LSTMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Padding sensitivity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Noisy with padding"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Ignores padding"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Visual analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Grading on a curve\" (student score depends on class average)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Grading against answer key\" (student score depends only on their answers)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Math: Layer Normalization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a single sample with "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " features:"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 1: Compute Mean and Variance (across features)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mu = \\frac{1}{d} \\sum_{i=1}^d x_i"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sigma^{2} = \\frac{1}{d} \\sum_{i=1}^d (x_i - \\mu)^2"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 2: Normalize"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\hat{x}_i = \\frac{x_i - \\mu}{\\sqrt{\\sigma^{2} + \\epsilon}}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\epsilon"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a small constant (~1e-5) for numerical stability.)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step 3: Scale and Shift"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y_i = \\gamma_i \\cdot \\hat{x}_i + \\beta_i"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "γ and β are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learned during backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "https://klu.ai/glossary/layer-normalization", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "klu"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Layer Norm Works: Step-by-Step Example"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single sample with 3 features:\nx = [2.0, 4.0, 10.0]\n\nMean: μ = (2 + 4 + 10) / 3 = 5.33\nVariance: σ² = ((2-5.33)² + (4-5.33)² + (10-5.33)²) / 3 = 10.89\n\nNormalized:\nx̂₁ = (2 - 5.33) / √(10.89 + ε) ≈ -1.02\nx̂₂ = (4 - 5.33) / √(10.89 + ε) ≈ -0.41\nx̂₃ = (10 - 5.33) / √(10.89 + ε) ≈  1.43\n\n(Now mean=0, variance≈1 for this sample)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each sample is normalized independently using its own statistics.)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Layer Norm Matters: Problems It Solves"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Works with Variable-Length Sequences"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Transformers process text of different lengths → padding required → Batch Norm stats distorted by padding zeros"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Layer Norm ignores other samples → padding doesn't affect normalization"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Batch Size Independence"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Batch Norm fails with batch=1 (variance=0 → division by zero)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Layer Norm works with batch size 1 → ideal for:\n- Fine-tuning LLMs (often batch=1)\n- Real-time inference\n- Memory-constrained settings"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. No Inter-Batch Dependency"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Batch Norm makes each sample's normalization depend on other samples in batch → no interference from unrelated sentences"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Layer Norm normalizes each token based on its own embedding → semantically stable"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Layer Norm"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers / LLMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (standard)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variable-length sequences, padding, batch=1 fine-tuning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RNNs / LSTMs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential data, no fixed batch stats"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CNNs / Vision"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "❌ Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed-size images, batch stats regularize well"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small batch size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm noisy with batch < 8"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size = 1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm crashes (variance=0)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Quick rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sequence models"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Transformers, RNNs) → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vision models"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (CNNs) → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch Norm"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Transformers Use Layer Norm (Not Batch Norm)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformers deal with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "text"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", which has special properties:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch Norm Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm Solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variable length"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Must pad → zeros distort stats"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ignores padding, normalizes per token"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Context-dependent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Other sentences affect normalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each token normalized independently"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch=1 fine-tuning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Crashes (variance=0)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works perfectly"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In a batch of sentences with different lengths, padding zeros would drag down the mean/variance for Batch Norm. Layer Norm calculates statistics using only the actual token embeddings."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\n# For Transformers / RNNs (feature dimension = embedding size)\nmodel = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Linear(512, 1024),\n    nn.LayerNorm(1024),  # Normalize across 1024 features\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Linear(1024, 512),\n    nn.LayerNorm(512),\n    nn.ReLU()\n)\n\n# Transformer encoder layer (standard)\ntransformer_layer = nn.TransformerEncoderLayer(\n    d_model=512,\n    nhead=8,\n    dim_feedforward=2048,\n    layer_norm_eps=1e-5  # Uses LayerNorm internally\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n\n# For Transformers\nmodel = models.Sequential([\n    layers.Dense(1024, input_shape=(512,)),\n    layers.LayerNormalization(),  # Default for Dense\n    layers.ReLU(),\n    layers.Dense(512),\n    layers.LayerNormalization(),\n    layers.ReLU()\n])\n\n# Transformer encoder (uses LayerNorm internally)\nencoder = layers.TransformerEncoder(\n    num_heads=8,\n    key_size=512,\n    dropout=0.1\n)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm Variants"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pre-Layer Norm vs Post-Layer Norm"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Transformers, Layer Norm can be placed:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Placement"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Post-LN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Transformer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Norm "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "after"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attention + FFN layers"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pre-LN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern (e.g., LLaMA, GPT-3)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Norm "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "before"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attention + FFN layers (better stability)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pre-LN advantage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": More stable training for very deep networks."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " normalizes across "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "features within each sample"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (horizontal axis), not across batch "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "https://klu.ai/glossary/layer-normalization", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "klu"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size independent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Works with batch=1, unlike Batch Norm"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Transformers, RNNs, LSTMs (sequence models with variable-length data)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not for"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CNNs/Vision (use Batch Norm instead)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solves padding problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Ignores padding zeros that distort Batch Norm statistics"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No inter-sample dependency"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each token normalized independently based on its own embedding"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Four steps"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": compute mean/var across features → normalize → scale (γ) → shift (β))"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Modern Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Pre-Layer Norm"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (before attention) for better stability"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Layer Norm is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "standard normalization in modern LLMs and Transformers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because it handles variable-length sequences, works with batch=1, and doesn't let padding or other samples interfere with normalization."}]}]}}